# 🧠 Concept 1: Distributed Event Streaming

🔥 One of the most used architectures in modern backend systems.

---

# First Understand the Idea

Instead of services directly talking to each other:

```text
Service A → Service B
```

they publish events.

---

## Example

E-commerce Website

User places order.

Event generated:

```text
Order Created
```

---

Multiple services react:

```text
Payment Service

Inventory Service

Notification Service

Analytics Service
```

---

## Real-World Analogy

News Channel 📺

A news channel broadcasts once.

Millions of viewers consume it.

The broadcaster doesn't call each viewer individually.

---

## Why Powerful?

✔ Loosely coupled systems

✔ Scalability

✔ Fault tolerance

✔ Real-time processing

---

## Connection

This extends:

* Message Brokers
* Kafka
* Event-Driven Architecture

that you learned earlier.

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why use event streaming?**

👉 Because producers and consumers become independent, improving scalability and flexibility.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Produce event

Many consumers react
```

---

# 🧠 Concept 2: Data Consistency Models

🔥 Very common system design interview topic.

---

## The Problem

Suppose:

Server A stores:

```text
Balance = ₹5000
```

Server B stores:

```text
Balance = ₹4000
```

Which one is correct?

---

## Different Consistency Models

---

### Strong Consistency

All users see latest data immediately.

---

### Eventual Consistency

Updates propagate gradually.

Eventually all nodes agree.

---

### Causal Consistency

Related operations maintain order.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Google Docs

Strong consistency:

Everyone sees edits immediately.

---

WhatsApp profile picture

May take time to update everywhere.

That's eventual consistency.

---

## Tradeoff

More consistency often means:

❌ Lower availability

❌ Higher latency

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why do distributed systems use eventual consistency?**

👉 To improve scalability and availability.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Strong = Immediate

Eventual = Later
```

---

# ⚙️ Concept 3: Memory Disaggregation

🔥 Extremely important future data-center concept.

---

## Traditional System

Each server owns:

```text
CPU

Memory

Storage
```

---

## Problem

One server may have:

```text
Free memory
```

while another runs out.

Wasteful.

---

## Solution

Memory Disaggregation

Pool memory across many servers.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Hostel rooms sharing one common library instead of each room buying separate books.

---

## Benefits

✔ Better resource utilization

✔ Flexibility

✔ Scalability

---

## Why Important?

Modern AI systems need:

```text
TBs of memory
```

Memory pooling becomes essential.

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why is memory disaggregation useful?**

👉 Because memory resources can be shared efficiently across servers.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Memory becomes a shared resource
```

---

